# INAIURAI v5.0 — AI Workforce-as-a-Service

## WHAT THIS IS

InaiUrai is a platform where customers hire AI employees. They describe a
business objective; InaiUrai dynamically assembles the right team of AI
executives (from 16 roles across 5 divisions), orchestrates their work,
and delivers structured results.

"Hire AI employees. Describe the outcome. We deliver."

## CORE CONCEPTS

### Engagements (Universal Work Unit)
Every interaction is an "engagement" with a mode:
- Task: 1 role, 1 request, 1 response (30-120 sec)
- Project: 2-6 roles, coordinated deliverable (hours-days)
- Department: 2-4 roles, ongoing with heartbeats (monthly)
- Company: 4-8 roles, build + operate (monthly)
Same codebase, same infra, different config parameters.

### Dynamic Team Assembly
Customer NEVER picks roles. They describe objectives.
Orchestrator (Claude) analyzes request → proposes team → customer approves.
Solo messages auto-route to best single role. No confirmation needed.

### Organization + Member (B2B-Ready)
Every B2C customer is an org of one. Every B2B company is an org of many.
Soul document splits: org_soul (company knowledge) + member_profile (individual).
All context is org-scoped. Members share the AI workforce.

### Agentic ReAct Loop
Claude decides what tools to call, observes results, self-corrects.
Every tool call → Permission Gate. Every iteration → Cost Governor.
Every step → Audit Trail. Web content → Firewall. Output → Validator.

### Five-Layer Security
1. Permission Gate (tool_proxy.py) — role tool allowlists
2. Prompt Firewall (firewall.py) — web content sanitized
3. Output Validator (output_validator.py) — leak detection, disclaimers
4. Cost Governor (cost_governor.py) — iteration/token/time limits
5. Audit Trail (audit.py) — append-only log

### Three-Tier Actions
- Tier 1 OBSERVE: web_search, read_url, recall_context (no confirmation)
- Tier 2 DRAFT: draft_email, draft_document (user must approve)
- Tier 3 EXECUTE: send_email (authorization + limits) — Phase 2

### Paperclip-Inspired Patterns
1. Goal Ancestry: every task carries the engagement objective, the role's
   purpose, completed dependencies, and downstream dependents in the system
   prompt. Agent knows WHY, not just WHAT. Passed via goal_ancestry dict.
2. Visible Reasoning Trace: /trace/{task_id} endpoint generates human-readable
   narrative from audit trail.
3. Per-Role Budget: each role in an engagement can have a monthly_budget_cents.
   CostMeter checks this before every iteration.
4. Atomic Task Checkout: tasks.checked_out_by prevents double-work in
   multi-agent engagements.
5. Heartbeat Pattern: roles in ongoing engagements wake on schedule, check
   for work, and deliver proactively.

## ARCHITECTURE

Channels (Telegram/Slack/PWA/API) → Go Backend → Python Engine → Claude API
                                        ↕
                                   PostgreSQL

## DATABASE TABLES
organizations, members, org_context, member_profiles, engagements,
tasks, role_catalog, agent_audit_trail, agent_sessions,
confirmation_requests, daily_cost_tracking, billing_events,
customer_credentials, contacts, scheduled_actions, message_log,
customer_channels, sms_log, capability_registry

## CONVENTIONS
- Go: net/http, lib/pq, uuid.UUID, context.Context first param
- Python: FastAPI, Anthropic SDK, all tools through ToolProxy
- Security: agent never calls external services directly
- Every engagement has an org_id. Every task has org_id + member_id + engagement_id.
- No bare except in Python — always catch specific exceptions or at least Exception
- Error messages to agents: type only, never internals. Full detail to audit.
- All Claude API calls wrapped in try/except with graceful fallback.
- All LLM-returned values (role_slug, engagement_type) validated against known sets.
